reviews: Great hotel. Very friendly people on reception and nice clean, modern rooms. Location is good, not too far from the metro and right opposite the street heading into the heart of foodie heaven. I would highly recommend this hotel. But be aware, the rooms, like most in Paris are not huge. But comfortably cosy.

I love the hotel! Everyone were so kind and helped with everything. The hotel room was perfect, really clean and everything worked perfectly. It was in a centric zone and very secure. I would stay here again!

This is a lovely hotel, it is very quirky and situated away from the main attractions and yet, is close enough to what you need to enjoy a visit. The rooms were lovely, with gorgeous decor and were clean although ours was quite small for a superior. The only negative I can mention is that although the female receptionists were helpful, the male receptionist on duty on our last evening / morning we left could have been more helpful and pleasant. Our airport transfer was running late and although we were sat in reception with him, he failed to mention this to us, until we approached him to see if he could follow it up for us. He did not say anything so it was a bit awkward, especially when your job is the tourist industry.

2 hours late checking in no toilet roll or products and bed had stains on it was average but dissatisfied
Will be returning ti Paris but not to this hotel we also paid extra fir something when we got there but wasnt explained to what it was for

Very nice hotel! Clean and comfortable. The staff was very helpful and friendly. Rooms are small but clean and comfortable. Location is good, close to Metro and lots of restaurants. Breakfast was good and Wyeth the price.

Thank you very much. I enjoyed my stay a lot. 100% recommendation.
Super tidy
Super friendly
All in all the best location to browse around Paris
Beloved neighbourhood
Lovely restaurants and cafs
We love it at this very perfect hotel

Hotel staff were helpful and courteous. Location was ideal and the hotel was stylish, clean and comfortable.

Breakfast option looked good but I was not available for breakfast. Pleasant environment
A room overlooking the street would have been nice but the one I had was lovely and quiet

I loved this charming hotel. Rooms were small but immaculately decorated, and had teamaking facilities. Staff were friendly and helpful. And the location, 2 minutes from Republique metro station, was excellent

Very clean and great staff. Great location for walking around Paris. The metro is also around the corner. Lots of cafes to choose from. Make sure to walk to the neighborhoods. We will be back to stay!

The hotel is well located to get about to do the sights, its beautifully clean and the decor is modern traditional. The room was small but that wasnt an issue as it had everything needed for a comfortable stay.
Just a few more hooks dotted around the bedroom and bathroom would have been helpful!

Such a lovely hotel, with absolutely sublime service. Friendly staff, great location and clean rooms. Comfortable beds and pillows.

Highly recommend and I will be staying here all times forward in Paris.

Friendly staff, comfortable and well-equipped room (v. small but in Paris this isn't unusual!). Easy access to nearby Metros and loads of bars and restaurants in immediate proximity, We loved Marais Home - only slight drawback was I'd emailed ahead to let the hotel know it was a trip for my partner's birthday (and his first time to Paris). I'd been promised a note and gift in the room but this wasn't arranged. Not a big deal, but a shame this wasn't followed up on. Lovely staff and lovely stay nonetheless and you cannot beat the location.

We experienced wonderful service at the front desk, a great location to walk to many great sights and restaurants, and a clean room. We would recommend and hope to return ourselves during a future trip to Paris.

The hotel is really what you need for a short romantic vacation in Paris. Good value for money. The hotel is very good located and is pretty cool. There are great bars within a few minutes walk. The hotel has a gym and a nice roof top. The young boss of the hotel is a fantastic help. She is efficient, helpful, and unobtrusive.

Quiet and clean. Friendly staff.
Very small room. Pricelevel too high for this.
Room was on the 5th floor, so it was quiet. But other (respectless) guests in hotel were easy to hear when theiy discussed late at night in corridor.

When we first arrived, we were given a room in the basement (level -1) which was very dark. I asked if we could change room and were told the hotel was full. Then the wifi didn't work in this room. Again asked if we could change but was told we could use the wifi in the lobby because the hotel was full. When I said it was unacceptable, the front desk said they would call the manager. 10 minutes later they said we could change to a room on the 4th floor (I thought the hotel was full!!). The room we were given was extremely small and of a lower category but we wouldn't get a refunded for the difference. So conclusion I paid for an expensive room and we ened up in a lower category room which costed less. This is by far the worst hotel I have ever stayed in and I am French. I can't imagine how they treat tourists.

Very nice place to stay in Paris: comfortable, nice, in a very good position with a super kind staff. Modern look, comfy room and with good services.
Also the breakfast is various and good quality. Recommend.

Room was so small you could pass another . Most of the outlets werent working , so no coffee unless you wanted to move the machine to another part , only one phone could be charged at bed , hair had to be done outside the bathroom. Some of the staff were a bit rude but not all . One insisted I leave my key during the day as he wanted to make sure who was using the room ( ???) . The bright side was Ruth the lady in charge of breakfast was a true doll, and the area was really cool with great shops and restaurants.

Excellent location in beautiful Marais. Easy access and small, but nice and clean room. Very friendly and helpfull staff. Breakfast also nice. We recommend Hotel Marais Home to everyone that is looking for small, but excellent luxury in Paris.

Nice room, the young girl at receptions was very kind and super fast check-in. We had an issue with the internet in our room and quickly came up to the room to check on it, it was partially fixed. It was nice to have windows on both sides and A/C

Location is perfect, short walk to Marais district, lots of great restaurants around, near Republica metro station. Rooms are small but clean, nice shower, air conditioner worked perfect.
One minor issue - we had a room on the first floor and you can hear subway underground. But it wasnt too much of a problem. Maybe ask for higher floor. And also one advice - dont go to the bouillon republique restaurant that is across the street. People are staying in line there but its the worst restaurant weve been to in Paris!

This hotel was perfect for my and my partners 5-night stay in Paris. The location was excellent, right around the corner from the metro and also very walkable. The room was small, but it was totally fine for us. The front desk staff was always super friendly and helpful. We used the rooftop twice, which was really nice. Wed definitely stay here again.

This was a very convenient little hotel for our visit to Paris and the front desk service was extremely friendly and helpful. Except--our shower drain was clogged and remained unresolved over the four nights we were there.

The Hotel is tiny!
If you are travelling with a baby or toddler avoid it. The hallways that lead to the rooms are super narrow and it can be very difficult to move a stroller around. ( even impossible)

The hotel is trying to provide an impression of high end design , which is nice, but, are forgetting to look into the details.

In the coach in our room was a very disgusting stain which made us avoid sitting there.

The bathroom was overall clean , but in the corners was showing clear stains that the cleaning is only superficial.

I very much enjoyed my stay at the Hotel Marais Home. The hotel was charming and well-maintained. Rooms were small but neat and cozy. Nice sitting areas in hotel. Good breakfast. All of the staff were friendly and helpful. Great for a solo traveller!

small room, a little bit dirty.

the closet was dirty inside and they did not make my room even putting the sign.

The receptionists are nice but they forgot to order my taxi.

The shower was nice. and the placement is really good

A good boutique hotel in a great location at a good value. I have stayed here a few times, and always had very friendly and helpful staff. The rooftop terrace is a nice place to get some respite from the bustle of The Marias. The rooms do what they need to. They are starting to age with slow draining showers, and a couple of broken door handles/lights, but still comfortable, cozy, clean and for me the perfect Paris location. While the prices seem to have risen, this is still a very good value hotel.

It's a decent hotel and in a good general location*. But it's not actually in the Marais, so the name of the place is misleading. Especially if you are truly looking for a Marais vibe.
*It's located near multiple Metro lines, and very close to some awesome neighborhoods. So while the location is great the actual STREET the hotel is on is very noisy and dirty. Yes, I know, Paris is a big city, etc. And some grime is to be expected. But this specific street is definitely not "cosy".

Staff was friendly and helpful. Nice small courtyard and roof deck. Room as small but that's Paris. Room service never replenished coffee pods or water bottles. But room was clean and AC worked great (it was really hot when we were there). Bathroom was clean and functional but shower was awkward.

Again though, hotel was clean, staff was nice, and area felt safe (if less than quiet).

This hotel is beautiful updated and the staff is so helpful. It has all the little touches that make it comfortable such as bath sheets for towels and great air conditioning. The area has many restaurants right next to it. Also you are close to 2 metro stations. It made our trip so memorable. I truly recommend this hotel and will stay their again if I am ever in Paris.

We spent quite a long time researching 3* hotels in Paris for this trip, having stayed in several previously. At this price bracket, in central (ish) Paris, you can get good quality but not luxury and all hotels will have at least some flaws. We werent in the Marais, but just a short walk away.
This hotel was very clean and well maintained -a bit corporate in feel, but with more tasteful use of colour and a touch of the almost-stylish here and there. Very comfortable beds (we had two different rooms) and high quality sheets. The rooms werent spacious and storage was not generous, but there was a suitcase rack in each room and the upgraded rooms have more space and had just about sufficient space to fit the yoga mat in. Staff all friendly and helpful.
Its on a busy street, so we didnt open the windows at night on the front of the hotel. Air conditioning worked well though.
Dont bother with the breakfast (we didnt have it but it looked just above basic) or expect much from the gym (just a few cardio machines). No fridges in rooms or ice available from reception though they put a bottle in their fridge for us. The electricity in the room goes off when you leave the room with your key (they only give you one) so you cant charge batteries etc. when out.

Great staff, who was always willing to help, before our stay via text and phone, and during our stay. Clean rooms, breakfast available at an extra cost, and a small gym on the lower floor.Appreciated having adapters and iron available.

very good hotel. Breakfast was more than enough; staff is very helpful, good tips and guidelines. We saw more of Paris. Typical resto's , galleries...The room was not very big but in the centre of Paris. Metro in the neighberhood.

We had a long weekend in Paris for some sightseeing. The hotel staff are extremely friendly and helpful. The breakfasts were very nice. The hotel was very clean. Our room was TINY in spite of having asked for a twin room rather than a double but we didnt need to spend too long in it so that was not a big issue in the end of the day. It is well situated between Filles du Calvaire and Rpublique mtro stations so access to the central attractions was not difficult. It was also well placed for wandering within the Marais district and for plenty of nice cafes and bistros.

The front desk staff was so nice and helpful. They gave so many great recommendations. The place itself was so amazing as well. Rooftop views were incredible and extremely clean space! Will come again

Excellent choice for a short stay in the heart of Paris. The staff and the amenities of the hotel are very good. The rooms are bigger than the average in Paris. Superior and Deluxe rooms are the best. Try to book the rooms on the 4th floor and up for supreme views and maybe small balcony

A nice place to stay, located next to Place de la Republique. Very loud and very small rooms. I mean SMALL. But nice stuff, very friendly and engaged. We would come back next time, but not in a room located towards the street

A very friendly, accommodating staff, lovingly decorated room, quiet but very central location! Unfortunately, we stayed only for one night. Therefore, we booked a standard double room with minimum equipment. There was no mini fridge in the room. We would have liked to put a few things in the fridge. But everything else was perfect. It was even possible to check-in a little earlier.

Nice service very kind people.
But room (triple superior) was VERY small. Almost no place to leave your luggage. Would have benefitted to have more space in terms of hooks etc. Very little room to store stuff.
Also very noisy on the side of the road, traffic goes on day and most of night as well.

Would be great if the Netflix app on the TV could be used.

Good location and breakfast, very nice people in the center of Paris. Bathroom was renovated and functional, room small but silent, bed comfortable. Breakfast fresh and with everything. Staff very helpful

Everything was perfect: good service, clean, modern and also the location is perfect (nice neighbourhood & close to metro and train station - TGV). Good price vs. quality. Breakfast is simple, but good. Would really recommend this hotel.

Very comfortable beds, the hotel is nicely decorated and very good service. The Hotel is in a great position to visit Paris with easy access to most attractions, rooms are small but the basics are well covered!

The hotel has comfortable, if somewhat small rooms and is well located just a few minutes walk from the Rpublique metro station, a few stops from Gare du Nord. There are plenty of independent local shops and places to eat and drink nearby, and you are on the edge of the attractive Marais quarter.

Nice hotel with small but very cute rooms in a very good location to explore Le Marais and Paris on foot with very friendly and helpful staff. Two small complaints that lost a star for the hotel. 1. The Wifi signal was very weak in our room and in todays day and age a ne marche pas! 2. The breakfast croissants were very uninspiring and it would be so easy to do better in this amazing city!

Great hotel in the center of the Marais district, very clean, very attentive staff and best hotel beds I've ever slept in. Had a very good stay for 4 nights. Warmly recommended hotel to stay at in Paris!

It is advertised as very good for price and quality. It is not so. Too expensive for very average. Very small rooms. Staff is very friendly. Location is ok, though being on a busy road. Breakfast is ok ish, nothing special.

The hotel is perfect for a city trip.
The regular rooms are very small but during a trip you dont need a lot of space as you will be outside most of the time.
The location is great and you csn walk to msny sights.
Gym in basement is nice too.

Awesome, friendly reception, great location for us. Busy street but with windows closed it was quiet. Great beds. Small but clean rooms. We had breakfast outside the hotel. Enough places to choose from.

This hotel is well positioned for tourist attractions and is walkable to Eurostar (30 minutes). The hotel was clean and enforced sensible Covid restrictions such as staggered timings for breakfast. The staff were friendly and recommended excellent restaurant choices.

This hotel is very well located from Gare du Nord and the Marais. Wonderful, cool bars & restaurants within a 5 minute walk. From the hotel we walked to the Louvre and Sacre Coeur. Rooms are very small but well equipped and super clean. Our room was quiet and dark so sleeping good. Beds very comfortable. The staff are charming and cant do enough to help. Overall a good value and good experience.

The manager was very accommodating when asking to change to a larger room. Very kind, and helpful. Would recommend staying there, and would love to come back! The hotel was under renovations, but was still charming and delightful to stay in!

Very friendly and helpful staff, who met every expectation we had. Our room was clean, modern, and had all the amenities we needed. The breakfast downstairs was tasty and had many options.
We would stay here again.

The hotel is very cozy and well organised. Double rooms are quite small but modern, extremely clean and well equipped. The team is lovely and super efficient, a special mention to the waitress working during breakfast time, she's adorable.
Breakfast room is just WOW and the little terrace at the roof top is definitely a plus thanks to that parisien view!

I had a really nice night in this Hotel Marais Home during the Corona time.
Well organised and calm place for resting and spending time in Paris.
Also great staff, totally recommendable!
I am very grateful!

Very good value for money. Good location, clean and safe. Next to the metro station La Place de Republique. Very friendly and nice staff! Nice beds and modern rooms. Nice showers, everything was great. Small rooms, but thats Paris.

very clean and well-kept hotel. near the metro station and in a nice quiet neighborhood.
very genitle staff and available for every need.
I was very impressed with the organization and the welcome kit as a consequence of what is happening at the moment

I recently spent 24 hours in Paris after a European beach vacation and my friend highly recommended that I stay in the Le Marais district. From the reviews, I would have thought that this hotel was much different than what it wound up being. I had a perfectly pleasant experience, but it was not what I was expecting. I thought I was going to be in a trendy hotel in a lovely Paris neighborhood (much like a chic hotel in the Soho or Tribeca area of NYC or Covent Garden in London) and that was not the case. The staff was perfectly lovely and accommodating  they allowed me to check in an hour and a half early and they also helped me book my ticket to Museum DOrsay so I could skip the line and didnt have to buy a ticket there. However the hotel is a bit more dank than I thought it would be  I had an incredibly small room that almost made me claustrophobic. Had it been appointed better, I dont think it would have bothered me as much, but because the aesthetic was really lacking and it was so small, it made the experience that much less appealing. The room felt very clean, but incredibly bare bones. (The night table was basically a tiny TV tray with hardly any surface area to place a book and a pair of glasses!) There was not even a luggage wrack to put a suitcase on (there would not have been space for one any way, as there was a closet with space for hanging clothes and shelves instead) and everything was a bit dated. There was also a shaggy dark carpet covering the whole room which seemed clean enough, but I much prefer hotels with hard wood floors so you can really assess the cleanliness. I was a bit skeeved out by the carpet and wore sandals the whole time to be safe. There was also absolutely no view and the elevator was so small only one person could fit in it comfortably. I asked the front desk for a bottle of water when I returned for the night after dinner, and they gladly gave me a lovely bottle of Evian, which I was charged for upon checkout. They considered it a mini bar purchase. For a hotel charging 250 per night, I think they should be able to accommodate their guests with a complimentary bottle of still water. It didnt break the bank to buy the water, in my opinion its just a lack of courteous accommodation that I would have expected from a hotel in Le Marais. The breakfast was also not included  they charge 14 or 16 for the breakfast buffet. Again, not expensive by any means, but that is something that really could be included in the price. I decided to go to a lovely boulangerie around the corner for breakfast and that wound up being a great choice. Overall the experience was just fine for what I needed, as I was only there one night and spent 10 hours out and about sight-seeing, so I was only in the room to freshen up upon my arrival and sleep before heading out to CDG. (A half hour drive with no traffic.) Overall it was a perfectly fine experience, but there were certainly no frills and I felt like I was in a clean but dated Best Western of Paris. If youre looking for something more elegant or trendy, this is not the place for you.

Stayed in hotel marais 6th - 9th March was suprised for my wifes birthday. I looked for around 3 weeks for hotel suitable for us and booked around 4 different one a before deciding on this one. Got hotel around 11.00 room wasnt ready as expected really so they kept bags safe till later. When eventually booked was on top floor deluxe room. Was very clean and decent size for Paris rooms. Bed was very comfortable and balcony with view of Eiffel Tower lit up at night. Staff excellent and breakfast too. Big plus for me could make my own boiled eggs as they are only way I eat them. Honestly could not fault hotel in anyway, had very pleasant stay would not hesitate stay there again.
Thanks hotel marais Home.

Clean comfortable well located excellent fresh food for breakfast- highly recommend.staff very attentive.great location for exploring the delights that Paris has to offer - either by foot or metro - which is only a few hundred meters away from the hotel

Although the rooms were small we enjoyed our stay at this well located hotel.
The staff was very friendly and helpful.
Unfortunately we did not have time to try the wellness offers of the hotel.
Very nice breakfast.

We had very high hopes for our stay in Paris at Hotel Marais Hme, however unfortunately a few things meant the stay in the hotel itself was in the end average. Firstly the first room we stayed in was very cramped and made it difficult to navigate around the room with 2 people staying. We paid for an upgrade for the remaining 2 nights and the room was much better in terms of size, but an AC system with no option for using it on fan only and only able to heat (winter mode) meant sleeping was a little uncomfortable. We also couldnt leave the window open for air circulation because the main road was quite busy and therefore noisy.

The plus point was by far the location, with shopping, restaurants and attractions (Louvre, Picasso museum) all within either a 20 minute walk or 10 minute scooter from the hotel. If the hotel could do something with their AC system, I would give it 4 stars, if the rooms were a little bigger then 5!

very friendly staff,
always ready to help, well located with walking distance to metro station, restaurants, and the Marais good confortable rooms, with all amenities to make ones stay a confortable one

The hotel is very near the place de republique and very easily accessible by metro (line 5 from Gare day nord). The staff are very friendly and speak good English and were kind enough to let me try out my French.The Marais home hotel is very clean , compact and comfortable and is a definite recommend and good value for central Paris

My stay at Hotel Le Marais Home has been pretty amazing, everything was very clean and all the services are excellent.

The size of the room is perfect for two and the amenities could not be better. Also, the gym is very nice and the breakfast is very complete for all kinds of diets

You get excellent value for your money at this budget hotel. The room does not have a single unnecessary square centimeter, and few frills. But it was perfect for a good night sleep. It was my second stay, and if I need a place in Paris, I'll stay there again.

Excellent location, 5 mins from Republic where several metro lines are available. It was good access from Gare de Lyon. I expected a bigger room for the price but 300 euros without breakfast during a weekend before fashion week may be a good deal.

Very good staff. room really very small anyway with a very comfortable bed
Breakfast was good and selected. The hotel is clean. Near republique underground. The arrondissement is not so far to the city center

I can highly recommend this hotel. The rooms were beautifully appointed, with a super comfortable bed, hot showers, with good water pressure. The staff were very attentive and friendly. It's in a central location with quiet rooms.

Excellent service! The staff were very friendly and helpful. Great location within walking distance from Paris EST, and many other sites. Had the Metro's been working, it would have been incredibly easy to get to all of the major site's. However, Uber was always available when we needed to get anywhere that was too far to walk in the chilly weather.

Friendly hotel, original rooms, small but ok for a few nights, very friendly staff; very close to le Marais. Rooms at inside patio can smell smoke from patio; beware if you book; we recommend the hotel!

The hotel is located a minute's walk from the Republic Square
The rooms are not large but comfortable and clean
Good breakfast at a fair price
Excellent customer service. Every receptionist we encountered always smiled, always helped, always advised. Perfect customer service.

The front desk service was excellent, by all service providers at all hours of the day.
We took a room without breakfast but one of the days we went down to eat - the payment was fair (compared to the cafes around) and the food was satisfying.
The bed was very, very comfortable.
There was an air conditioner that worked very well.
We were upgraded to a deluxe room and it was gratifying.
The location of the hotel is good, we got along well during the train strike.
The center of the lively Mara district can be reached between 600 meters and a kilometer. We were also able to reach other tourist areas without a problem.

A number of things that are missing / problematic:
There was cold coming out of the window beside the bed - the cold was felt at night to those who slept on this side of the bed (the windows probably did not close well or were not well sealed).
There was no minibar in the room and it is a shame because there is a coffee machine but there is no where to store milk for those who want. And there were no tall glasses of coffee with milk.
The room was small (and this is also a deluxe room).
The hotel staff did not fill the bathtub soap (but we did not ask).

Overall very pleasant and reasonably priced hotel and service was really excellent

Loved the hotel. Room was perfect, nice and big and very clean. Staff was very friendly and helpfull. Made us feel very welcome and at home. Location was really good, near subway and the centre of Paris. Would greatly recommend this hotel!

Great location..right beside republica square and subway. Plenty of restaurants and nightclubs within walking distance.staff very friendly and helpfull would definitely recommend staying here.and will be back.

This was a 2nd time stay in the hotel and all was a good as previous. Excellent rooms, great and helpful staff, brekkie a highlight (actually has hot foods too). Is very close to Republique METRO and many restaurants.

We had a great weekend in Paris, staying at the Hotel Marais for 3 nights. Very pleasant hotel with great staff, nicely done rooms (small but with done with creativity). And good access to Metro. Recommended.

The Hotel Marais Home was a wonderful hotel experience. First is the location. Away from tourists, but close to a large metro stop (Republique), and within a short walk of a couple of others. The nearby Republique square is a lively spot, with plenty of restaurants and bakeries to enjoy. Most of the people in the area seemed to be locals, which makes this hotel centered on a truly authentic Parisian neighborhood. You wont find the large tourist attractions outside your door, but we had no problem traversing the city within minutes on the Metro.

Second, the hotel itself is simply lovely. The modern decor wraps itself around the older brick interior of the building. The front desk staff, of which we saw at least four (maybe more) different employees working during the week, were very friendly. They all spoke English which is nice for those of us who lack advanced French.

They have a beautiful little breakfast area. We encountered two different employees working the area during our stay, both were very nice. The food is pretty good, we ate there every day. There should be something for everyone for breakfast, from croissants and baguettes, to eggs, sausage, cereal, juice, and yogurts. The rooftop terrace was nice to check out, but we stayed up there only briefly. If you look up at night, and look closely, you will notice the spotlight from the Eiffel Tower passing by.

Third, the room was modern and charming. We got a two level room with a spiral staircase. It is true that compared to American hotel rooms it is smaller. We liked it even more for that reason. Lack of space makes for a creative room. The bathroom was modern, the bed made for an amazing afternoon nap (after our redeye filght) with soft covers and pillows, and the tub on the upper level made for a relaxing cozy space.

Do your trip a favor and stay here. It is not steps away from the tourist traps, but it is steps away from real Paris, and that is what we came to see.

This small hotel is a really cozy one. The people are very friendly and helpful. The small gym is very clean. I loved doing yoga there. You can book the sauna and steamroom for yourself for a very good price. My room was very clean and cozy. I slept like a baby. It was the perfect stay!

I understand small hotels but if you are going to have a hotel in paris for $300 a night please at least design them better (like Tokyo) - I could not fit my suitcase on the floor and walk to the bathroom because the bed and the wall were inches from each other. I do want to state that the staff was very friendly and helpful but the accommodations were disappointing to say the least, would not recommend.

The location is nearby to pretty much everything - cafes, metro, etc. The hotel itself was clean and the staff helpful. For a short stay you get all the ameneties without burning a hole in your pocket.

We travel to Paris yearly and have stayed mostly on the 7th arr and central Marais area. I must say this stay was very pleasant because of the professionalism of the staff. I can only remember Xavier's name but all of them have been patient, helpful and knowledgeable. The daily interaction, asking how our stay is and making sure everything was OK really made up for a few days residence at the Citadines Place d'Italie. Hotel Marais Home is lcated <15 min walk from central Marais- Place de Voges, Picasso Museum, Holocaust Memorial, Breizh Cafe, you name it is within a comfortable walking distance. No hills, just cobblestones so leave your stilettos at home. Two blocks away from the beautiful Place de la Republique, cafes, restaurants and a couple of Metro stations are within stone's throw away. The rooms are standard for Paris so don't expect a Vegas size space. It may seem small to your average American traveller but it worked really well for my husband and I. The staples are in the room including a Nespresso coffee maker, daily clean sheets, great air-conditioning (a must in the summer time), and a nice quiet space to chill after seeing Parisian sights. Sadly, I forgot about the rooftop terrace. Will definitely check it out when we return next year... And yes, we will go back to this place. For the price, convenience, great reception staff, you cannot beat that.

Our family loved hotel Marais. The rooms were small however the beds were very comfotable, great showers, excellent coffee provided in the room and Republic train station walking distance. Xavier at the front desk was very helpful.

This was our second stay at the hotel Home Le Marais. We enjoyed a long family weekend with our grown up children in Paris. We all liked the hotel, the location and the area. The staff is very friendly, helpful and gave excellent recommendations for local restaurants nearby. We will certainly come back again.

We stayed in the suite on the 6th floor.Very comfortable' modern design with good facilities and bathroom and with great view of the Sacre- Coeur and the tip of the Eiffel Tower. Excellent and helpful reception staff. Good breakfast. Perfect position on the northern border of the Marais and easy walking distance to museums and attractions in the area. Lots of cafes, restaurants and bars to choose from close by.Pefect for Paris!! But the WiFi needs to be improved -very faulty most times.

This is Paris, so an extremely small room in a relatively central hotel, wasnt entirely unexpected, even for nearly 500 for 3 nights. It smelled distinctly stale on arrival. The bed and pillows were comfortable and clean.

Friendly reception staff whenever I spoke with any of them.

Roof terrace is small but nice to sit on late afternoon.

Basement gym is more focused on lighting and exposed brickwork than any useful equipment. No free-weights or resistance machines. Not worth bothering.

The light in the shower began flickering if used for more than a few minutes - not good if you are epileptic! I reported it to the front desk but it wasnt addressed during my stay.

The sink in the bathroom had a musty smell - perhaps due to the overflow being clogged and dirty.

The front desk wanted to charge me 10 for an adapter, but after a little coaxing, agreed to loan me one for my 3 nights, which I returned.

Couldnt find an English language tv channel. First 20 were all French and there was no guide in the room, so I gave up.

There is a small kettle, with 2 tea bags and 2 mills. No coffee. Nothing was replenished during my stay.

This is such a great Parisian hotel! We had a three person room and I was so impressed by the size, amenities, quality of the bed/pillows/linen and the helpful, cheery staff. Coming home after a long day of touristing felt serene and relaxing. Will definitely stay here again.

Yes, as others have pointed out, the rooms here are small. But I challenge you to find a centrally located, reasonably priced hotel anywhere in Paris where this is not the case. So having gotten that out of the way, this is a great option in Paris. It's within walking distance of tons of Marais restaurants & cafes and within very easy walking distance of a major metro hub, from where you can easily get to all the major sights.

The rooms are modern & clean, the beds & pillows are comfortable. All of the staff we encountered were friendly & helpful. With all the great pastry shops in the area we didn't bother to try the breakfast. WiFi was weak at best, so that's the one area of improvement I would suggest. Otherwise, a great stay, we would not hesitate to go back.

Overall our stay here was pleasurable. Most importantly, we were greeted well and provided with lots of useful information. The room is small and we struggled to get our four cases in as we were travelling down to Antibes afterwards. It is doable though and they state the room sizes clearly on their website. The hotel is placed close to a Metro station and is only 20-25 mins walk to the Seine. The room was comfortable and looked recently refurbished. The staff were excellent, from the front desk to the ladies serving breakfast, which was also a pleasurable experience.

Nice deco and location. Small rooms, small lounge and vending machine, small roof terrace and patio ( for smokers???) Clean room and bed. basic breakfast; everyday the same. 7x 24 reception staff is friendly but distant. No personal touch, feeling like a number stayed for 4 nights.

They charged my credit card 2.5 times the amount they were allowed to / my room costed.
They say ill get it back... lets hope they dont lie.
The room was ok, but very very small and high priced.
The outflow of the sink didnt work and on some items like lamps there was a huge amount of dust.
The employees were very friendly and the location was good.

Nice, clean, cosy room.
Excellent breakfast.
Very pleasant personnel.
Good location, close to metro station, lot of cafes nearby, always some people on the street.
Would recommend it to everyone coming to Paris.

We had a very nice time. The hotel is in a great location in the middle of lots of interesting neighborhoods. If you love to walk and explore, it is perfect. It is also right at a train station which made farther away destinations easy to get to. The staff was very helpful and the room was petite but very cute. I would go back!

comfortable bed. Clean with very nice breakfast.
Friendly front desk personnel that were helpful (Abraham especially).
Lost hot water for one day which was inconvenient.
Could walk to many good restaurants from this location
Felt safe

We had a nice stay, but shower was really to small. This should be changed. We stayed in the Duplex room so maybe it is better to have a bigger shower in the bedroom instead of a bath. And the breakfast room is to small for 30 rooms

Very nice hotel in a really convenient location. Staff is very friendly, post-booking experience very modern and pleasant, place is clean, not too noisy (inside room, not street-facing), breakfast is worth the extra expense.
One downside is that even though the standard room is small, the wifi signal is not consistent and sometimes it disappears altogether. Oh and sockets only on one side of the bed.
Other than that there's nothing I can fault. Recommended.

The Hotel Marais Home was the perfect place to relax after a day of exploring Paris and celebrating Bastille Day. The balcony gave us amazing views of not only the city but we also saw some of the fireworks from the celebration! The staff were so welcoming and treated us like friends. I would recommend this beautiful place that is near restaurants, transportation, and shopping to everyone.

Had a fantastic stay here and would highly recommend to anyone wanting an alternative to a chain hotel that feels very French, clean, modern, funky, comfortable with very good breakfast (in a very quirky and lovely room) and very friendly & helpful staff. We loved it and would definitely stay here again.

Location: Very convenient from the Rpublique station, where several lines cross. But it is also steps from the Oberkampf and Filles du Calvaire stations.

There are a bunch of fantastic Boulangerie nearby - Aux Pchs Normandes and Boulangerie Utopie were two of our favorites. Two of the best craft cocktail bars, Le Mary Celeste and Little Red Door, are a stone's throw from its front door. Also, a pharmacie, a bank, a post office, two Wild & The Moons (vegan spot), wonderful bistrot and cafes, The Fringe Coffee, and more. You can easily walk to the shopping district near the Muse Pablo Picasso and National Archives.

The room was very cozy, and most importantly for us, had both windows and A/C. The ventilation and temperature control were really comforting after a long day hiking hundreds of Eiffel/Montmartre/Arc stairs. We didn't partake in any of the amenities - but they have a rooftop for champagne drinking, a breakfast bar, a lounge, a sauna, and English-speaking staff.

I would stay here again in a heartbeat!

But I dont know if it would be good for families, as the room was pretty small and the elevators are really slim.

Really friendly and nice little hotel - one i will, certainly use on a regular basis. Great part of Paris and clean and with a nice feel about the place. Staff are really friendly and incredibly helpful.

Loved this area in Marais! Not so crowded as many others and had great cozy restaurants and bars. Very easy metro ride to every spot we wanted to go in Paris as first time visitors. Clean and very cute hotel with staff onsite 24/7 so you don't even have to carry your key around with you. Fast WiFi.

Great rooms with great concierge and the room was absolutely clean especially the bathroom which was very modern I Loved everything .
Though it was very small
Its common for European rooms . My room can probably hold only 2 people max.
